ProtoResult:
. "{\bf (Law of Large Numbers for Ergodic Markov Chains)} Let 
   $H_j^{(n)}$ be the proportion of times in $n$ steps that an 
   ergodic chain is in state $s_j$. Then for any $\epsilon > 
   0$, $$ P\Bigl(|H_j^{(n)} - w_j| > \epsilon\Bigr) \to 0\ , $$
   independent of the starting state $s_i$."
